<subSubSection id="209CE1E20DCCFCF635ED74C964EDF076" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="77453302517B76096E5948BABADCC6C7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="72A414908442925D18F625FF70232786" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Twining perennial of unknown height, glabrous in all vegetative parts. Leaves petiolate, 3-4 
<normalizedToken id="8A5E46E5ED60D624D467C6CE4FA0AF21" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.3-2.2 cm, deltoid, finely acuminate, shortly mucronate, base truncate to cordate with rounded auricles, margin denticulate, abaxially paler with prominent veins; petioles very slender, curved, 9-17 mm. Inflorescence of solitary pedunculate, axillary flowers; peduncles 10-15 mm; bracteoles caducous, not seen; pedicels noticeably stouter than peduncles 12-15 mm; sepals subequal, elliptic, glabrous, margins scarious, outer 8-11 
<normalizedToken id="1FB8E5FCAD4FBA4774593326E6AB759C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-6 mm, obtuse, inner 9-12 
<normalizedToken id="FFDFCE7585C715802C4FF9E82269B22C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-7 mm, rounded, usually c. 0.5 mm longer and 1 mm wider than outer sepals; corolla c. 5.5 cm long, pink, glabrous, funnel-shaped, limb 3-3.5 cm diam. Capsules 13 
<normalizedToken id="F087FB41B5B3D5275A495BE8B9D2A320" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-7 mm, conical, glabrous, strongly rostrate, the apex 4-5 mm long, persistent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
