<subSubSection id="9FF7C994830BC8ACD79B6177C6C1F220" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="F96A778D5759EC5091A5652D2ADD0241" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B848CFFCD8AAE4EEFAEDAEEBDCD50305" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Almost certainly related to 
<taxonomicName id="02F8E027C7BF572D28BF434E2AA3ADF6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procumbens">
<emphasis id="B313A66ADCB52F2F559B8E8D72CDBFDF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea procumbens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="67E768AE721C97A7C26D1AD9BFE3AE34" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longirostra">
<emphasis id="646036C8ED16268B878AE4D2C50AB11D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. longirostra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by its ovate-deltoid, basally truncate leaves which are borne on slender pedicels. The subequal sepals are ovate-elliptic with distinct scarious margins, rather different from the lanceolate to ovate, usually acute to acuminate sepals of 
<taxonomicName id="C1B57E4858B50D7872C37376227D9543" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procumbens">
<emphasis id="04C35235D2165B8D5585A389C648694F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. procumbens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The strongly rostrate capsule of the new species is also striking.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3F8FB84137BFD2B73956601AB09651DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="741B3DFF2FEF3148F4E40DF87B039D29" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C.R. Sperling et al. 6050</emphasis>
(FTG, K, MG, NY) from Serra dos 
<normalizedToken id="AE3879BF1CF38096AD0D0049EBB67C1D" originalValue="Carajás">Carajas</normalizedToken>
in 
<normalizedToken id="92C3BE04B3BEA44FAB153CE11BE8619A" originalValue="Pará">Para</normalizedToken>
State may belong here but the inflorescence is branched and no fruit was seen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
